## Scope Calculator Logic

### Complexity Calculation

```javascript
complexity = 'low'    // 1-2 products, straightforward
complexity = 'medium' // 3-4 products, moderate integration
complexity = 'high'   // 5+ products, complex requirements
```

### Timeline Estimates

**Low Complexity (1-2 products):**
- Timeline: 2-4 weeks
- Dev Hours: 40-80 hours
- Team: 1 developer
- Phases: Setup (1 week) â†’ Build (1 week) â†’ Test (1 week)

**Medium Complexity (3-4 products):**
- Timeline: 4-8 weeks
- Dev Hours: 120-200 hours
- Team: 1-2 developers
- Phases: Setup (1 week) â†’ Core Build (2-3 weeks) â†’ Integration (1-2 weeks) â†’ Test (1 week)

**High Complexity (5+ products):**
- Timeline: 8-12 weeks
- Dev Hours: 240-400 hours
- Team: 2-3 developers
- Phases: Architecture (1 week) â†’ Core Build (3-4 weeks) â†’ Advanced Features (2-3 weeks) â†’ Integration (1-2 weeks) â†’ Test & Launch (1 week)

### Adjustment Factors

**Increase timeline/complexity if:**
- Customer has legacy systems
- Requires custom reconciliation
- Multiple account types (business + consumer)
- High transaction volume (>1M/month)
- Complex error handling requirements

**Decrease timeline/complexity if:**
- Using Plaid's quickstart templates
- Standard use case (no customization)
- Existing Plaid integration (adding products)
- Strong engineering team

